text: Just saw Searching 2 hrs ago, and it is an amazing movie of the year. I would totally give it a 5/5 stars, GO SEE IT!!!  Honestly, I was not intending to see this movie at the first place. The plot have a sequence of unexpected twists and humorous moments, I enjoyed the whole 1hr and 45 so min because everything happens so fast and new information reveals every minutes. If you are going to watch this movie, then NO SPOILERS !!! beforehand will give you the best experience.   I can't stop taking and thinking about the plot. I still recommend it to psychological thriller fans if you didn't seen the better movies like Shutter Island, Unsane, and Girl Gone. And Prisoners. text: Am I the only one who found this predictable!? WOW. As soon as the police detective came on the scene, I guessed it all. That her son was a psychopath who she was covering for. There were a couple of tells. One being that Fish & chips had no profile photo and then also the model profile photo, how dismissive she was on that and accentuated certain things in her tone as if she was trying to cover something up!! Turns out I was right. Him putting her laptop back in the home was overall stupid/pointless. In an attempt to make it seem as if she didn't go missing right away. All he had to do was continue texting the dad, to make him think she's still responding. Check the texts & take the trash out as if everything was normal to buy time without him investigating. No wonder she wanted to keep her low IQ psychopath out of jail, she wasn't much different to him to be honest. I get he was her son but that girl was this guy's daughter. I also wondered if that was the reason she became a detective, to cover up for her son. Well yeah. The other tell for me was her story about how her son went around scamming people, how she covered for him. I then was on to her that she was now doing the same but for a bigger crime. Don't ask me how I know these things, I just do. So to me there were no plot twists and turns like people say. I was quite bored and disappointed in how bad the writing & acting was. The only thing maybe someone could give perspective on is why did she go to the funeral on her own, without the dad? I felt like it was a bit more then attendance to make sure everyone assumed she died, something else was going on. The only thing I couldn't predict is that his daughter would have survived in the end. Regardless of the rain, still didn't know it would mean her survival as she could have gone into shock due to injury or suffer from hypothermia once temperature drops and being out there wet in the cold, or died from injury as in hitting her head. I would go as far to say the detective herself had cold and callous traits. The moment she showed up I sensed she wasn't normal, maybe that's how they told her to act for the scene but I knew and the rest of the movie was like really. That said, major fail imo. Plot twist my ass! Just call me detective meow.
